Mods.Name: Trophy Unlock All
Mods.Description:
Make sure to follow instructions for this to work!

1. Install this
2. Restart the PS3
3. Load any Game and wait until you are at the main menu
4. Press PS button then press R1+O, again press the PS button wait for 10 Seconds then Press select button
Boom!! All trophies Should Pop-up


Warning!!
1st - I turned off Save Data Owner in my Debug settings.
idk if this actually did anything because I turned it off when I first couldn't get the trophies to stick but then they didn't stick again so I kept it off and continued...

2nd - Go onto the game you are trying unlock trophys for OFFLINE and start unlocking trophies.

3rd - Once all the notifications stop, sign in and click on your name on the far right so you can view your profile and it should say it is syncing your trophies and boom! Your trophies should be synchronized!

Mods.Name: Orignal PS3 FW 0.91 (4.xx) (Waves & Coldboot)
Mods.Description:
I've been trying to recreate the very first wave ever from PS3 FW 0.91.

This is very close to it IMO. Try it out and let me know what you think.

I extracted the 0.91 wave and took all the shaders (vpo/.fpo) and preset files (MNU) and the spline.elf and rebuilt a wave that works on 4.40+ FW, maybe even lower, not tested. This lines.qrc will work on CFW or HEN, or even OFW if you have a way to get the file on to your system like for example a web exploit like HAN.



It took me quite a while to make as I had to test each vpo and fpo one by one to see which ones worked. Some causes a soft brick so it was a bit of a tedious job.

Note: This has black backgrounds forced for every month/time of day and there are no particles available (just like 0.91 FW). I recommend choosing the first color in theme settings and setting the theme and background to 'classic'


My PVR does not show the exact color very well, it looks better in real life IMO. Try it out. :)

Many thanks to @pink1 for his work on Xforge, without him this would not have been possible, and thanks to @Proto for making all the videos of the old XMBs from preretail FW.

EDIT: Added 2 variations:

- One has the normal preset forced all the time so the wave will not change when in music player, coldboot, gameboot etc
- The other has the coldboot2 preset forced always which looks really nice too.
